wifi: mt76: mt7925: restore FW_DWLD_BYPASS_DMASHDL in MT6639 PM wake path

mt6639_dma_init() sets FW_DWLD_BYPASS_DMASHDL (BIT(9) of GLO_CFG)
during initial probe, but mt792x_dma_enable() - called on every PM
wake cycle - did not restore it. On MT6639, every CLR_OWN causes the
ROM to reinitialize WFDMA which resets GLO_CFG. The PM wake path
already restores ADDR_EXT_EN and clears CSR_LBK_RX_Q_SEL_EN but was
missing FW_DWLD_BYPASS_DMASHDL.

Add FW_DWLD_BYPASS_DMASHDL to the existing is_mt6639() block in
mt792x_dma_enable() so all three MT6639-specific GLO_CFG bits are
consistently restored after PM wake.

Assisted-by: Claude Code <noreply@anthropic.com> [claude-opus-4-6]
Signed-off-by: Javier Tia <floss@jetm.me>
---
diff --git a/mt792x_dma.c b/mt792x_dma.c
index 04c0663..14178bd 100644
--- a/mt792x_dma.c
+++ b/mt792x_dma.c
@@ -184,7 +184,8 @@ int mt792x_dma_enable(struct mt792x_dev *dev)
 
 	if (is_mt6639(&dev->mt76)) {
 		mt76_set(dev, MT_WFDMA0_GLO_CFG,
-			 MT_WFDMA0_GLO_CFG_ADDR_EXT_EN);
+			 MT_WFDMA0_GLO_CFG_ADDR_EXT_EN |
+			 MT_WFDMA0_GLO_CFG_FW_DWLD_BYPASS_DMASHDL);
 		mt76_clear(dev, MT_WFDMA0_GLO_CFG,
 			   MT_WFDMA0_GLO_CFG_CSR_LBK_RX_Q_SEL_EN);
 	}
